
[1]calm

   CALM, a.

   1. Still; quiet; being at rest; as the air. Hence not stormy or
   tempestuous; as a calm day.

   2. Undisturbed; not agitated; as a calm sea.

   3. Undisturbed by passion; not agitated or excited; quiet; tranquil; as
   the mind, temper, or attention.

        CALM, n. Stillness; tranquillity; quiet; freedom from motion,
     agitation, or disturbance; applied to the elements, or the mind and
                                  passions.

     CALM, v.t. To still; to quiet; as the wind, or elements; to still,
             appease, allay or pacify, as the mind, or passions.
